====Verb====
{{en-verb|pays|paying|'''[[paid]]''' or '''[[payed]]'''}}

# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[give]] [[money]] or other compensation to in exchange for goods or services.
#*{{quote-magazine|date=2013-06-21|author={{w|Oliver Burkeman}}
|volume=189|issue=2|page=48|magazine={{w|The Guardian Weekly}}
|title=[http://www.theguardian.com/technology/2013/may/10/conscious-computing-twitter-facebook-google The tao of tech]
|passage=The dirty secret of the internet is that all this distraction and interruption is immensely profitable. Web companies like to boast about{{...}}and so on. But the real way to build a successful online business is to be better than your rivals at undermining people's control of their own attention. Partly, this is a result of how online advertising has traditionally worked: advertisers '''pay''' for clicks, and a click is a click, however it's obtained.}}
#: {{usex|lang=en|he '''paid''' him to clean the place up;&nbsp; he '''paid''' her off the books and in kind where possible}}
# {{context|ambitransitive|lang=en}} To discharge, as a debt or other obligation, by giving or doing what is due or required.
#* Bible, Psalms xxxvii. 21
#*: The wicked borroweth, and '''payeth''' not again.
#*{{quote-magazine|date=2013-06-22|volume=407|issue=8841|page=68|magazine={{w|The Economist}}
|title=[http://www.economist.com/news/finance-and-economics/21579860-g8-pledges-tackle-three-ts-t-time T time]
|passage=Yet in “Through a Latte, Darkly”, a new study of how Starbucks has largely avoided '''paying''' tax in Britain, Edward Kleinbard [&hellip;] shows that current tax rules make it easy for all sorts of firms to generate what he calls “stateless income”: [&hellip;]. In Starbucks’s case, the firm has in effect turned the process of making an expensive cup of coffee into intellectual property.}}
#: {{usex|lang=en|she offered to '''pay''' the bill;&nbsp; he has '''paid''' his debt to society}}
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To be profitable for.
#: {{usex|lang=en|It didn't '''pay''' him to keep the store open any more.}}
# {{context|transitive|lang=en}} To [[give]] (something else than money).
#* {{w|William Shakespeare}}
#*: not '''paying''' me a welcome
#: {{usex|lang=en|to '''pay''' attention}}
# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} To be [[profitable]] or worth the effort.
#: {{usex|lang=en|crime doesn’t '''pay''';&nbsp; it will '''pay''' to wait}}
# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} To discharge an obligation or debt.
#: {{usex|lang=en|He was allowed to go as soon as he '''paid'''.}}
# {{context|intransitive|lang=en}} To suffer consequences.
#: {{usex|lang=en|He '''paid''' for his fun in the sun with a terrible sunburn.}}

